EXPLANATION OF FEES AND CHARGES
WATER
The charge for water used is measured by the water meter. The charge is based on each 1,000 gallons of water used or a portion thereof
plus a base rate charge dependent upon the size of the water meter, effective for billing issued as of 10/1/2012.
WASTEWATER
The charge is based on each 1,000 gallons of water used or a portion thereof plus a base rate charge dependent upon the size of the
water meter.
HYDRANT MAINTENANCE
The charge to maintain hydrants throughout the town.
MISCELLANEOUS
As of 10/01/2020, if applicable, a surcharge for those meters that have not been converted to the new remote read system.
TRASH
The flat rate charged by the town for the collection and disposal of solid waste per each single family residence and/or unit.
STORM WATER
Federal mandate requires the town to monitor and improve processing of runoff storm water.
INDIANA SALES TAX
State Sales Tax collected on water and hydrant. Also collected on miscellaneous fees, if applicable.
PENALTIES
-> Water delinquent fee is $10 or 10% whichever is greater.
-> Sewage delinquent fee is 10% of unpaid balance.
-> Stormwater delinquent fee is 10% of unpaid balance.
-> Trash/Solid Waste delinquent fee is 10% of unpaid balance.
-> Now, delinquency date for all charges are the same.
GENERAL INFORMATION
BILL PAYMENT
Bills may be paid by mail, in person at the Town Hall, at First Financial Bank branches, or by placing the payment in the drop box
located in the parking lot at the Town Hall. For your conveience, a Direct Withdrawl Automatic Payment Plan is available.
Failure to make payment in full by the due date will result in penalties being assessed.
ESTIMATED BILLS
If the letter 'E' follows your meter reading, your read was estimated according to the water works rules and regulations
(Rule 1.18.1(B)(!) availble online.
UNPAID BILLS
The Town of Highland reserves the right to disconnect service for non-payment of bill. A service fee and total amount due
must be paid before services will be resumed.
MOVING OR DISCONNECTING SERVICE
Please call 972-7589 Monday thru Friday for final meter reading at least 24 hours prior to moving.
EMPLOYEE IDENTIFICATION
For your protection, every town employee carries an official identification card bearing his or her name and photograph.
Please ask to see this card when an employee vists your home.
